Ask HN: Do any Bluetooth virtual device/splitter apps exist on iOS or Mac?
text: I've started testing out some rowing apps recently, specifically EXR (like zwift but for rowing) and asensei which is a coaching app. I was hoping to do an asensei workout whilst having EXR in “Just Row” mode but both apps require a bluetooth connection to the Concept2 PM5 monitor which will only connect to one app. I thought there would likely be an app which would allow you to create Virtual Bluetooth devices and route an existing stream to it, similar to Rogue Ameoba’s Audio Hijack or Midimittr on iPhone but I can’t find anything.  This would allow me to connect the PM5 to the app and then have the data relayed to both applications. The closest thing I’ve found seems to be an app called LightBlue but I don’t think it quite does what I want (I will be able to confirm tomorrow). Does anyone know of anything for iOS or Mac that will do the job or is this not technically feasible?

Ask HN: Do we still have educators like Jacob Bronowski?
text:
Any contemporary broadcaster or educator who comes even close in terms of education, trust in the intelligence of their audience, and sheer balls?

I'm refering here to the creator of the 1973 series "The Ascent of Man", and am thinking particularly of the Auschwitz scene [0].

Although I'm primarily looking for people who are active today, references to older works that you think are in the same league are also welcome.

[0] https://youtu.be/ltjI3BXKBgY?t=210

title: Ask HN: Which old, functional, electronics do you have?
